paragraphs.text:
%md
# Can Business Rule be removed

In the current implementation of the smart push noticiations we have both a business rule (20% heavy users per tag) and the ALS scores.
In this note I check whether the business rule recommendations are redundant by checking whether they are also part of the ALS scores.

paragraphs.title: General code to retrieve scores from s3
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.sql.Encoders
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._

case class ScoreOnDisk(srcUniqueId: String, dstUniqueId: String, score: Double, source: String)
val scoreSchema = Encoders.product[ScoreOnDisk].schema


def readScores(scoreName: String) = {
    spark
        .read
        .option("header", "true")
        .schema(scoreSchema)
        .csv(s"$scoreName")
        .withColumnRenamed("srcUniqueId", "tag")
}

val scoresCount = scoresJoined
    .withColumn("isPresent", when($"source".isNull, lit(0)).otherwise(lit(1)))
    .groupBy("tag")
        .agg(
            sum($"isPresent").as("present"),
            count(lit(1)).as("total")
        )
    .withColumn("missing", $"total" - $"present")
    .orderBy($"total".desc)
